                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17200602-17-off83 t17200602-17-cd84"></join> last. The Prosecutor deposed that he lay down on the Bed to sleep, and that the Prisoner (a Girl) lay in another Bed in the same Room; that when he lay down he had the Guineas together in a Paper in one Pocket, and the Silver loose in another Pocket, and when he rose both were gone: That he found the Prisoner next Day at Mr. Ogden's at the Crown in Southwark, who confest that she had taken it, and gave Mr. Ogden 5 Guineas and Half a Crown, and had spent 2. Guineas that Night; that 
